1
00:00:05,024 --> 00:00:09,104
We see that we live
in a circumstance

2
00:00:09,104 --> 00:00:18,635
where there is mundane, inanimate
lifeless things, matter,

3
00:00:18,881 --> 00:00:26,430
and then there are conscious,
spiritual beings.

4
00:00:26,491 --> 00:00:29,064
[God Has Senses]

5
00:00:29,356 --> 00:00:34,262
So, when we deal with
the aspect of consciousness,

6
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:39,477
consciousness never exists
independently of personality.

7
00:00:41,384 --> 00:00:47,225
It cannot exist 
absent of personality.

8
00:00:48,623 --> 00:00:52,970
So we see, here are the many
conscious beings.

9
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:55,823
We were talking about this
earlier today,

10
00:00:55,823 --> 00:01:01,690
if (I gave the example)
I see someone,

11
00:01:01,690 --> 00:01:03,184
look at all the people 
in this room,

12
00:01:03,184 --> 00:01:06,104
they have two eyes, a nose,
two ears and a mouth.

13
00:01:06,104 --> 00:01:10,573
So, I can, without becoming
a research scholar,

14
00:01:10,573 --> 00:01:16,343
scientist, or any such thing,

15
00:01:16,343 --> 00:01:19,072
or with advanced degrees
in education,

16
00:01:19,072 --> 00:01:25,572
I can assume that
your mother, your father,

17
00:01:25,572 --> 00:01:29,103
they had two eyes, two ears,
a nose, a mouth,

18
00:01:29,103 --> 00:01:31,171
more or less.

19
00:01:31,864 --> 00:01:35,023
It’s safe for me
to assume that.

20
00:01:35,023 --> 00:01:37,989
So when I see
all these many beings

21
00:01:37,989 --> 00:01:41,223
who possess these different
types of characteristics,

22
00:01:41,223 --> 00:01:43,463
I could make a case and say,

23
00:01:43,463 --> 00:01:46,581
“Well, the original source
of all such beings

24
00:01:46,581 --> 00:01:52,817
must be similar. Someone
with eyes, ears, you know …

25
00:01:52,817 --> 00:01:56,141
who can see, touch,
taste, smell, feel.”

26
00:01:56,141 --> 00:01:59,572
We see in this world
observable characteristics,

27
00:01:59,572 --> 00:02:02,083
and these people who
have these abilities.

28
00:02:02,083 --> 00:02:05,482
They’re searching for something
beautiful to see,

29
00:02:05,482 --> 00:02:08,481
for someone beautiful to see,

30
00:02:08,481 --> 00:02:13,032
for someone beautiful to touch,
to hold, to interact with.

31
00:02:13,032 --> 00:02:15,229
They like to hear
beautiful sounds,

32
00:02:15,229 --> 00:02:21,297
taste pleasing substances …

33
00:02:21,297 --> 00:02:23,658
These are just normal things

34
00:02:23,658 --> 00:02:25,820
that everyone likes to do.

35
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:30,299
So I could understand,
the original source

36
00:02:30,299 --> 00:02:34,432
of all these types of beings
who enjoy these things,

37
00:02:34,432 --> 00:02:38,383
must also have those
kind of tendencies:

38
00:02:38,383 --> 00:02:41,223
to see, hear, taste,
touch, smell, feel;

39
00:02:41,223 --> 00:02:43,543
in other words,
to interact with others

40
00:02:43,543 --> 00:02:46,995
in a loving, affectionate way,

41
00:02:46,995 --> 00:02:50,275
as people are apt to do 
in this world.

